  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice <strong>half</strong> the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add the <strong>diced red onion</strong> to a medium bowl with the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]<strong> </span>sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>quick-pickled onion</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining onion</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
